<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1969,2031]" lastBlockId="24.[151,1437,153,540]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1969,1995]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Esper, 1792)" authorityName="Esper" authorityYear="1792" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[325,748,1969,1995]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="glaberrima">
<emphasis box="[325,584,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Leiopathes glaberrima</emphasis>
(Esper, 1792)
</taxonomicName>
is the oldest name within the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1896" box="[1186,1335,1969,1995]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Leiopathidae</taxonomicName>
, and has been mistakenly reported for several localities (
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[701,912,2005,2031]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="52 - 64" refId="ref48095" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2011) A new species of Leiopathes (Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the Great Meteor seamount (North Atlantic). Zootaxa, 3138 (1), 52 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3138.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Molodtsova, 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M." box="[926,1227,2004,2031]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="277 - 289" refId="ref50406" refString="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M. (2015) Description of a new species of Leiopathes (Antipatharia: Leiopathidae) from the Hawaiian Islands. Zootaxa, 3974 (2), 277 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3974.2.11" type="journal article" year="2015">Wagner &amp; Opresko, 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The species was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Baron-Szabo, R. C." box="[323,685,153,179]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref49259" refString="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Baron-Szabo, R. C. (2001) Re-descriptions of the antipatharian corals described by EJC Esper, with selected English translations of the original German text. Senckenbergiana Biologica, 81, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2001">Opresko &amp; Baron-Szabo (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, based on the specimens collected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brook, G." box="[1115,1269,153,179]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref46539" refString="Brook, G. (1889) Report on the Antipatharia collected by HMS Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Zoology, 32, 1." type="journal volume" year="1889">Brook (1889)</bibRefCitation>
, since the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,153,179]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
is incomplete. The specimen described here presents terminal branchlets with a slightly thicker basal diameter than that described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[351,566,225,251]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="52 - 64" refId="ref48095" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2011) A new species of Leiopathes (Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the Great Meteor seamount (North Atlantic). Zootaxa, 3138 (1), 52 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3138.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Molodtsova (2011)</bibRefCitation>
(up to 
<quantity box="[648,749,224,251]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
in our specimens, and about 
<quantity box="[1079,1180,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="0.22">0.22 mm</quantity>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[1217,1424,225,251]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="52 - 64" refId="ref48095" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2011) A new species of Leiopathes (Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the Great Meteor seamount (North Atlantic). Zootaxa, 3138 (1), 52 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3138.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Molodtsova, 2011</bibRefCitation>
), but within the range provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Baron-Szabo, R. C." box="[528,888,261,287]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref49259" refString="Opresko, D. M. &amp; Baron-Szabo, R. C. (2001) Re-descriptions of the antipatharian corals described by EJC Esper, with selected English translations of the original German text. Senckenbergiana Biologica, 81, 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="2001">Opresko &amp; Baron-Szabo (2001)</bibRefCitation>
(
<quantity box="[904,1045,260,287]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.7 mm</quantity>
). The present record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="glaberrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Leiopathes glaberrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(off 
<collectingRegion box="[333,501,297,324]" country="Cape Verde" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
), reinforces the tropical/temperate distribution indicated for this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M." pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="277 - 289" refId="ref50406" refString="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M. (2015) Description of a new species of Leiopathes (Antipatharia: Leiopathidae) from the Hawaiian Islands. Zootaxa, 3974 (2), 277 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3974.2.11" type="journal article" year="2015">Wagner &amp; Opresko, 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,153,540]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,368,395]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Distribution.</emphasis>
Wide geographic distribution, with 
<typeStatus box="[758,806,369,395]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Mediterranean Sea, Naples Sea (
